By comparing the AUPR of baseline and neural models with and without the graph structure, a key observation can be drawn that for both, the SVM classifier and the neural models, model performance increases when taking into account the underlying network structure of the data (PPI). Another interesting observation is that introducing pathway pooling translates into a decrease in performance for all models. This could be a result of the incomplete pathway knowledge on the PPI network. The PPI network used in this work has \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
